					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of approximately 12th to 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>236 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>279</height>
										<width>235</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>28 quires of 8 leaves, 1quire of 6 leaves, last 8 leaves of uncertain gathering. First leaf of the first quire missing and the last leaf of the third quire has been cancelled; two leaves probably missing at the end of the manuscript. </p>
									<p>One leaf has been cut after folio 231 and 232 respectively.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" writtenLines="37" ruledLines="37">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>The writing stands a little below the ruled line.</p>
									<p>The mishnah of each chapter is not divided into small sections as in printed editions of the Talmud, but is given in entirety before the gemara begins. </p>
									<p>Each chapter of the Mishnah ends with the phrase: סליק פרקא, and a few words of the mishnah are repeated as a heading to the gemara that treats on that part.</p>
									<p>Each chapter of the Gemara ends with: הדרן עלך.</p>
									<p>Each tractate ends with: סליקא מסכת.</p>
									<p>Folios 23r, 71r are left blank due to the fact that folio 23 and 71 respectively begin fresh quires written by different hands from the portions which in each case precede them, so that a new scribe began a new tractate. The concluding portions of the preceding tractates have been left out.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc>
							<summary>Sefardi square script, executed by many hands.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">Sefardi square, three or more different hands.</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Marginal notes in various parts of the manuscript, supplying different and at times fuller readings.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<p>BM/BL in-house binding.</p>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house. Harleian coat of arms on the upper and lower cover.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Rashi on the Pentateuch. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Harl. Or. 5508.'</p>
							</binding>
